<i>noun</i>: 유행성 [유행썽], 유행병 [유행뼝], 역병 [역뼝], 돌림병 [돌림뼝], 돌림 [돌림] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>유행성 [유행썽]</dt><br>
<dd>epidemic</dd><br>
<dd>주로 질병이 짧은 시간 동안에 널리 퍼지는 성질.</dd><br>
<dd>The trait of, mostly a disease, being spread widely in a short period of time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>유행병 [유행뼝]</dt><br>
<dd>1. epidemic</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 지역에 널리 퍼져 여러 사람이 돌아가며 옮아 앓는 질병.</dd><br>
<dd>A disease that is widely spread in a region, where many people contract it in turn.</dd><br>
<dd>2. blind follower</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 좋지 않은 유행을 무턱대고 따르는 경향.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A tendency to follow a bad trend without thinking much.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>역병 [역뼝]</dt><br>
<dd>epidemic; plague</dd><br>
<dd>치료하기 어려운 악성 전염병.</dd><br>
<dd>A malignant contagious disease that is difficult to cure.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>돌림병 [돌림뼝]</dt><br>
<dd>epidemic</dd><br>
<dd>다른 사람에게 전염되어 여러 사람이 돌아가며 걸리는 병.</dd><br>
<dd>A contagious disease that spreads among people.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>돌림 [돌림]</dt><br>
<dd>1. taking turns; rotation</dd><br>
<dd>차례대로 돌아감.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of alternating.</dd><br>
<dd>2. turns; rotation</dd><br>
<dd>차례대로 돌아 전체를 돈 횟수를 세는 단위.</dd><br>
<dd>The unit for counting the number of rotated turns.</dd><br>
<dd>3. epidemic</dd><br>
<dd>다른 사람에게 전염되어 여러 사람이 돌아가며 걸리는 병.</dd><br>
<dd>A contagious disease that has spread among people.</dd><br>
<dd>4. common syllable in the names of family members</dd><br>
<dd>같은 조상을 둔 후손들을 세대별로 구분하여 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A common syllable put in names in order to show that those persons are related by blood.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>